# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Vue 3 project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` (v2.0.0) - The official Vercel Speed Insights package
- Installed `vue-router` (v4.6.4) - Required peer dependency for the Speed Insights Vue integration

### 2. Configuration
The SpeedInsights component was already present in the codebase (`src/App.vue`) with the correct import statement:
- Import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/vue"`
- Usage: `<SpeedInsights />` component placed at the root of the template (line 2)

This follows the official Vercel documentation for Vue integration found at https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart

### 3. Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights and vue-router dependencies
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package versions and dependency tree

### 4. Verification
- ✅ Build completed successfully with `npm run build`
- ✅ No errors or warnings during compilation
- ✅ All dependencies properly resolved
- ✅ SpeedInsights component correctly imported from `@vercel/speed-insights/vue`
- ✅ Component properly integrated into the Vue application

## Implementation Details

The SpeedInsights component was integrated according to the official Vue-specific instructions:
1. The component is imported from `@vercel/speed-insights/vue` (Vue-specific entry point)
2. It's placed at the root level of the App.vue template for site-wide tracking
3. The component automatically tracks Web Vitals metrics and sends them to Vercel

## Next Steps for Deployment

To start collecting Speed Insights data:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for your project
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Once deployed and users visit the site, performance metrics will appear in the Vercel Speed Insights dashboard

## Technical Notes
- The vue-router package was required as a peer dependency even though the app doesn't use routing. This is because @vercel/speed-insights/vue optionally integrates with vue-router when available.
- The Speed Insights component is lightweight and won't impact page load performance
- Data collection only happens in production environments when deployed on Vercel
